    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-30T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-30T05:00:00-05:00" n="182"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/825.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-30T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>New-born enthusiasm tends to extravagant expenditures. If China is saved she must
                    be protected from financial improvidence. Indiscriminate borrowing and reckless
                    competition between bankers should be prevented. The plan suggested in your
                    March 19, 7 p.m., tends to that end and justifies monopolistic feature, which
                    may be regulated by friendly nations. It affords bankers fixed compensation,
                    secures their experienced service, and gives China benefit of the markets. The
                    agency term, ten years, will carry China over reorganization period. I am
                    disposed therefore to approve the plan in principle but am not committed to all
                    its details.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
